# jxl_phone_highfreq_phase2_2026-05-26.tsv

Phase-2 probe: can phone-aware HIGH-FREQUENCY-TARGETED relaxation save
bytes vs a global distance bump, without objectionable artifacts?

Tracks (all encoded with cjxl-rs --effort 7, scored vs ORIGINAL ref
under standard_4k [desktop] + modern_oled_phone_indoor [phone]):
- A_baseline : encode original at distance D (global RD knob)
- B_edgepres : selective-blur 0x1+10% (edge-preserving hi-freq trim) -> encode
- C_lowpass  : gaussian 0x0.7 (clean low-pass) -> encode

IM intermediates written as `-strip -depth 8 PNG24:` (REQUIRED — default
convert PNG output carries a color chunk that cjxl-rs mis-applies,
collapsing JOD 9.86 -> 6.81; PNG24 round-trip is bit-identical).

RESULT (iso-bytes vs baseline phone-JOD):
- photo_general (textured): both trims WORSE than baseline distance knob
  (-0.04 edgepres, -0.10 to -0.15 lowpass). Pre-trimming high-freq throws
  away quality the encoder would have allocated better.
- photo_dark (low-detail):  trims marginally BETTER (+0.01 to +0.05),
  tapering to tie at higher byte budgets.

CONCLUSION: preprocessing-based high-freq targeting does NOT reliably
beat the encoder's own RD allocation. It loses on detailed content,
marginal-win on flat/dark content. EPF override is also inert (encoder
auto-tunes it; sweeping --epf -1..3 at d4.5 moved bytes ~3%, JOD <0.01).

IMPORTANT LIMITATION: preprocessing operates OUTSIDE the RD loop and is
frequency-cruder than DCT-band quant. A negative preprocessing result
does NOT prove in-loop high-band quant scaling would fail. The genuine
phone-aware lever — scaling high-band DCT quant weights by the target
display's CSF cutoff (phone ~110 ppd pushes image high-freq past the
~40 cpd CSF falloff) INSIDE the RD loop — remains UNTESTED. It is the
only mechanism that could relax just-past-cutoff frequencies while
keeping the encoder's smart spatial bit allocation; a global distance
bump scales the whole matrix and can't do that independently. That work
requires jxl-encoder's high-band quant internals (DO-NOT-TOUCH in
tuning.rs + currently behind the broken cvvdp-loop feature).

Phase-1 companion: jxl_phone_vs_desktop_rd_2026-05-26.tsv (the phone's
high-freq forgiveness is real, ~20% photo saving, but captured by the
distance knob alone).
